\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\Berreman\\\\OpticalConstructor\\\\OpticalConstructor.Storage\\\\schema\\\\optical-constructor-project.schema.json\", \"limit\": 60}\n[tool Agent] {\"description\": \"Research optics ray diagram conventions\", \"prompt\": \"I'm writing a software spec for a schematic 2D optical ray-diagram drawing surface (top-down schematic of a...\nI have strong codebase and research context. Let me check the `.gitignore` (for the committable-JSON UX-checklist item) and the app entry point.\n[tool Bash] {\"command\": \"cd \\\"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\" && echo \\\"=== root .gitignore (patterns that could collide with a committable groups/collections JSON) ===\\\" && cat .gitignore 2>/dev/nu...\nLet me read the remaining files I intend to cite (AppShell, ProjectFile, SchemaValidation) so every pointer is verified before I commit it.\n[tool Read] {\"file_path\": \"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\Berreman\\\\OpticalConstructor\\\\OpticalConstructor.Ui\\\\AppShell.fs\"}\n[tool Read] {\"file_path\": \"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\Berreman\\\\OpticalConstructor\\\\OpticalConstructor.Storage\\\\ProjectFile.fs\"}\n[tool Read] {\"file_path\": \"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\Berreman\\\\OpticalConstructor\\\\OpticalConstructor.Storage\\\\SchemaValidation.fs\"}\nLet me confirm the absence of existing localization infrastructure (a load-bearing \"net-new\" claim) before I commit it.\n[tool Grep] {\"pattern\": \"resx|CultureInfo|Localization|Localized|ResourceManager|IStringLocalizer|i18n|\\\\.ru\\\\.|languageCode|translations\", \"path\": \"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\Berreman\\\\OpticalC...\n[tool Grep] {\"pattern\": \"CultureInfo|Localization|ResourceManager|i18n|languageCode|translations\", \"path\": \"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\Berreman\\\\OpticalConstructor\", \"output_mode\": \"content\", \"-...\nI now have all verified pointers and research. Let me check the project schema's element-related defs once more, then write the spec.\n[tool Read] {\"file_path\": \"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\Berreman\\\\OpticalConstructor\\\\OpticalConstructor.Storage\\\\schema\\\\optical-constructor-project.schema.json\", \"offset\": 160, \"limit\": 45}\nI have everything I need. Now I'll write the structured spec.\n[tool Write] {\"file_path\": \"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\specs\\\\0026\\\\.spec-md\", \"content\": \"# Spec 0026 — Optical Constructor UI (element/ray model, top‑down table, ribbon shell, groups, EN/RU)\\n\\...\nNow let me append the decision to `.history` via the safe writer. First I'll write the payload to a temp file in the allowed `.artifacts` folder.\n[tool Write] {\"file_path\": \"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\specs\\\\0026\\\\.artifacts\\\\spec-author-summary-0026.txt\", \"content\": \"Authored the structured .spec-md for Spec 0026 (Optical Constructor UI) ...\n[tool Bash] {\"command\": \"cd \\\"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\" && python -m ai_strategy_generator.spec_writer.history_cli append --spec-folder \\\"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\\specs\\\\0026\\\" --at \\\"2026-06-05T...\n[tool Bash] {\"command\": \"cd \\\"C:\\\\GitHub\\\\Berreman\\\" && python -c \\\"import json; lines=open('specs/0026/.history','r',encoding='utf-8').read().splitlines(); print('total lines:', len(lines)...\nThe spec is authored and the history row landed cleanly. Here's what I did.\n\n## Summary\n\nI examined the existing `OpticalConstructor` F# / Avalonia + FuncUI codebase and researched optics ray‑diagram conventions, then wrote the structured `specs/0026/.spec-md` from the finalized feature list. The `.spec-md` was previously empty; it now contains the full contract.\n\n**Codebase grounding (Read‑verified before citing every pointer):** beam tree + element kinds (`BeamTree.fs`), project aggregate (`Project.fs`), units spine (`Units.fs`), snapshot undo/redo (`History.fs`), the existing *cross‑section* schematic (`Schematic.fs` — deliberately not repurposed), the MVU shell/nav (`Shell.fs`, `AppShell.fs`), settings store (`UserEnvironment.fs`), JSON storage + schema validation (`ProjectFile.fs`, `SchemaValidation.fs`), and CTA styling (`ConstructionView.fs`). I confirmed by grep that EN/RU localization is genuinely net‑new.\n\n**Spec shape:** Part 0 binding constraints → the two **CRITICAL — land first** parts (A: element geometry/placement/rotation domain model; B: ray model, snapping, Snell schematic tracing) → top‑down table & drawer (C), ribbon/menu shell (D), centralized command model (E), catalogue + value‑id placeholder (F), groups + multiple detectors + separate storage (G), collections (H), EN/RU localization (I), standardized controls (J), undo/redo + safety (K). It closes with the six operator‑facing UX commitments (and an explicit N/A for the spec‑writer hidden‑controls checklist, since this is a desktop app), Acceptance criteria, Files in scope, Test artifacts, and References.\n\n**Key decisions made (recorded in the spec, not punted):** R2‑measured‑from‑incident‑ray with the `r2 + R2` law and R3 non‑orthogonality; LP/CP both map to the existing `Polarizer` case with the `Analyzer` case left untouched (resolving the codebase‑vs‑feature‑list tension with clear precedence); concrete default box dimensions, ray‑bundle radius (0.4×), and drawing weights drawn from researched conventions; groups/collections JSON at the per‑user app‑data path (sidesteps any `.gitignore` collision); value‑id picker explicitly out of scope with only a working empty modal committed.\n\n**Web research** fed the four \"Details left to the spec‑author\" items — drawing weights, schematic element/reflection rendering, default box dimensions, and the groups/collections JSON mapping — with citable anchors (ricktu288 ray‑optics defaults, SPIE/Zemax chief‑vs‑marginal conventions, WCAG C40 for the active‑element indicator, clear‑aperture≈2–3×beam for the bundle radius).\n\n**Scope:** edits limited to `.spec-md`, `.history` (one `spec`/`output` row via `history_cli`), and `.artifacts/` (the temp payload). No files outside the allowed scope were touched.\n\nOne note: as in prior cycles, `history_cli` only accepts `spec|claim-check|gates|handoff` for `--intent`, so I used `--intent spec` (matching the bundle's precedent) rather than the prompt's `spec` literal — which here align anyway.\nThe spec is authored and the history row landed cleanly. Here's what I did.\n\n## Summary\n\nI examined the existing `OpticalConstructor` F# / Avalonia + FuncUI codebase and researched optics ray‑diagram conventions, then wrote the structured `specs/0026/.spec-md` from the finalized feature list. The `.spec-md` was previously empty; it now contains the full contract.\n\n**Codebase grounding (Read‑verified before citing every pointer):** beam tree + element kinds (`BeamTree.fs`), project aggregate (`Project.fs`), units spine (`Units.fs`), snapshot undo/redo (`History.fs`), the existing *cross‑section* schematic (`Schematic.fs` — deliberately not repurposed), the MVU shell/nav (`Shell.fs`, `AppShell.fs`), settings store (`UserEnvironment.fs`), JSON storage + schema validation (`ProjectFile.fs`, `SchemaValidation.fs`), and CTA styling (`ConstructionView.fs`). I confirmed by grep that EN/RU localization is genuinely net‑new.\n\n**Spec shape:** Part 0 binding constraints → the two **CRITICAL — land first** parts (A: element geometry/placement/rotation domain model; B: ray model, snapping, Snell schematic tracing) → top‑down table & drawer (C), ribbon/menu shell (D), centralized command model (E), catalogue + value‑id placeholder (F), groups + multiple detectors + separate storage (G), collections (H), EN/RU localization (I), standardized controls (J), undo/redo + safety (K). It closes with the six operator‑facing UX commitments (and an explicit N/A for the spec‑writer hidden‑controls checklist, since this is a desktop app), Acceptance criteria, Files in scope, Test artifacts, and References.\n\n**Key decisions made (recorded in the spec, not punted):** R2‑measured‑from‑incident‑ray with the `r2 + R2` law and R3 non‑orthogonality; LP/CP both map to the existing `Polarizer` case with the `Analyzer` case left untouched (resolving the codebase‑vs‑feature‑list tension with clear precedence); concrete default box dimensions, ray‑bundle radius (0.4×), and drawing weights drawn from researched conventions; groups/collections JSON at the per‑user app‑data path (sidesteps any `.gitignore` collision); value‑id picker explicitly out of scope with only a working empty modal committed.\n\n**Web research** fed the four \"Details left to the spec‑author\" items — drawing weights, schematic element/reflection rendering, default box dimensions, and the groups/collections JSON mapping — with citable anchors (ricktu288 ray‑optics defaults, SPIE/Zemax chief‑vs‑marginal conventions, WCAG C40 for the active‑element indicator, clear‑aperture≈2–3×beam for the bundle radius).\n\n**Scope:** edits limited to `.spec-md`, `.history` (one `spec`/`output` row via `history_cli`), and `.artifacts/` (the temp payload). No files outside the allowed scope were touched.\n\nOne note: as in prior cycles, `history_cli` only accepts `spec|claim-check|gates|handoff` for `--intent`, so I used `--intent spec` (matching the bundle's precedent) rather than the prompt's `spec` literal — which here align anyway."}
